iplanet hosts are incompatible with such a\ndistribution (p~10^-6). This suggests that high obliquities are confined to\nhot-Jupiter systems, and provides further evidence that hot Jupiter formation\ninvolves processes that tilt the planetary orbit.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 18 Feb 2013 21:00:02 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 14 May 2013 12:41:20 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
